From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 07:54:21 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/tests/core-kunit: catch test failure in
 test_commit_dests_for()

Otherwise, NULL dereference.

The issue was discovered [1] by Sashiko.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260713144757.39740-1-sj@kernel.org

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/tests/core-kunit.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/damon/tests/core-kunit.h b/mm/damon/tests/core-kunit.h
index 097642be6b55e..fbe4272f669f2 100644
--- a/mm/damon/tests/core-kunit.h
+++ b/mm/damon/tests/core-kunit.h
@@ -1046,6 +1046,8 @@ static void damos_test_commit_dests_for(struct kunit *test,
 	skip = false;
 
 	KUNIT_EXPECT_EQ(test, dst.nr_dests, src_nr_dests);
+	if (dst.nr_dests != src_nr_dests)
+		goto out;
 	for (i = 0; i < dst.nr_dests; i++) {
 		KUNIT_EXPECT_EQ(test, dst.node_id_arr[i], src_node_id_arr[i]);
 		KUNIT_EXPECT_EQ(test, dst.weight_arr[i], src_weight_arr[i]);
-- 
2.47.3

